We just found this place tonight. Absolutely loved it (& I’m not a vegetarian nor eat that healthy usually), but this place is my new favorite! Loved the Salmon poke bowl, vegan chocolate cake, açaí bowl & delicious smoothie too! Can hardly wait to go back tomorrow for more great food! Next up...a wrap & the soup & carrot cake.

One of the most FRIENDLIEST staff I.ve ever seen! Hats off! The ladies in the front are very nice, very attentive! Theres also a tall guy who manages take-outs, he is very kind and nice! I come here everyday for a cup of orange juice for my nephew, and end up ordering couple different drinks. Their Pina Colada Smoothie is MUST TRY! Moreover, their menu is also crowded with whole bunch of salads, healthy treats, smoothies, juices, bowls, sandwiches and lot more. They always offer free sample drinks, juices! We used to order from neighbouring eateries but now only Sproutz! I strongly recommend! Keep doing well, Crew!

I am a huge fan and eat here on the regular. It is the only truly healthy place around the area. BUT I will have to say, since they made the change from Carrot Express the quality in the food has gone down a bit. I hope that you guys can take this criticism to help your business as I am someone who used to order every week and now I do sparingly.  The chicken is very, very dry and very plain, not seasoned at all. When cutting into the chicken it is still a bit pink inside.  I stopped ordering the wraps because the chicken is so dry that it ruins the entire meal even after dumping a whole sauce cup on top of it. The platters used to come with super fresh pico de gallo and a nice portion…Today, there is a spoon full of pico (mostly juice from the tomato) and the tomatoes seem not as fresh as I have seen in the past. The Cilantro lime dressing is now thick and lumpy; it used to be light and smooth.  Lastly, the red onions that you put in the chicken salad now turn your chicken bright pink…I almost dumped the dish out because it looked like uncooked chicken. (Just something to take into consideration.) I truly believe these are easy fixes that you should take seriously as I have been getting the same feedback from others. Thank you and I hope to be a regular again!
